 Unless explicitly compensated for, introducing a new channel into the main
 airstream will increase the airspeed at the outlet, which may be undesirable
 for some organisms or experiments.
 A simple way to compensate for this increase in the aistream is to use
 another valve to switch between an additional clean aistream and the odorised
 stream, as in Fig.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
